OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782123503
OL,3,CPeston: PM hasn't decided to quit, or
OL,4,Cat least not yet, despite Trump's
OL,5,C'scoop'
OL,7,FCabinet minister tells me that,
OL,8,Fdespite Donald Trump's "scoop", the PM
OL,9,Fhas genuinely not made a decision to
OL,10,Fquit, or at least he hasn't yet.
OL,12,FThe minister says that if Keir
OL,13,FStarmer's wife Vic were to encourage
OL,14,Fhim to fight on, he might just do that
OL,15,F- though the minister assumes there is
OL,16,Fa low probability of such an outcome.
OL,18,FAll this says to me that my Friday
OL,19,Fjudgement still holds, that the
OL,20,Funcertainty could drag on to Tuesday,
OL,21,Fthough presumably not longer.
OL,26,@pD@XOUpD@^O]
